text: Aaron Chatman (born 11 May 1987) is an athlete from Australia. He is disabled. He competed in the 2008 Summer Paralympics in Beijing, China and won a silver medal in the men's High jump--F44/46 and a bronze medal in the men's 4 x 100 metre relay--T42-46 race. Irina Dvoskina was his coach. == References == Category:Australian athletes Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Australia Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Australia Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:2008 Summer Paralympics
